title: Check if a health condition affects your driving

heading_context: Check if a health condition affects your driving
chunks.html_content: You need to tell DVLA about some medical conditions as they can affect your driving.
chunks.plain_content:
Check if a health condition affects your driving
You need to tell DVLA about some medical conditions as they can affect your driving.

heading_context: Check if a health condition affects your driving
chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you do not tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving.
chunks.plain_content:
Check if a health condition affects your driving
You can be fined up to £1,000 if you do not tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving.

heading_context: Check if a health condition affects your driving
Check if your condition needs to be reported
If you have a bus, lorry or coach licence
chunks.html_content:
You can voluntarily give up your licence. You might choose to do this if, for example:

  • your doctor tells you to stop driving for 3 months or more
  • your medical condition affects your ability to drive safely and lasts for 3 months or more
  • you do not meet the required standards for driving because of your medical condition

You’ll need to tell DVLA and send them your licence.

If you have a medical condition that affects your driving and do not voluntarily give up your licence, you must inform DVLA. They will decide if you can continue holding a driving licence.

If you have a car or motorcycle licence, you can either:

  • use the online service to check if your condition needs to be reported
  • check the A to Z list for your condition

You’ll then be told how to report your condition - this will either be in the online service or by printing off and sending a paper form.

You cannot use the online service to check for your condition or report it to DVLA.

Check the A to Z list for your condition and follow the link to find the form.

heading_context: Check if a health condition affects your driving
chunks.html_content:
You can use this service to search for your health condition and find out how to report it.

Some conditions can be reported in the service, and others need to be reported by printing off and sending a paper form.

heading_context: Check if a health condition affects your driving
chunks.html_content: This service is also available in Welsh (Cymraeg).
chunks.plain_content:
Check if a health condition affects your driving
This service is also available in Welsh (Cymraeg).

heading_context: Check if a health condition affects your driving
What you’ll need
chunks.html_content:
You’ll need to enter some details about your current driving licence and your condition.

To search for the condition, you’ll need to say what type of licence you have and confirm your entitlement to drive.

If you’re checking for someone else, and you do not know the information about their licence, you can check the A to Z list for the condition.

If you report your condition to DVLA through the service, you might need to give your GP or consultant’s name and address.
chunks.plain_content:
Check if a health condition affects your driving
What you’ll need
You’ll need to enter some details about your current driving licence and your condition.
To search for the condition, you’ll need to say what type of licence you have and confirm your entitlement to drive.
If you’re checking for someone else, and you do not know the information about their licence, you can check the A to Z list for the condition.
If you report your condition to DVLA through the service, you might need to give your GP or consultant’s name and address.

heading_context: Check if a health condition affects your driving
Use the service
chunks.html_content:
You’ll have one hour to add information once you start. You cannot save and return to your application later.

You can only use this service if you have a car or motorcycle licence. If you have a bus, lorry or coach licence, check the A to Z list for your condition instead.

Start now
